    "body": "### Problem\n\nHello,\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/e8a6c1b02122852da83dc52184e78369598d8240/src/nvim/ex_getln.c#L2706-L2709\n\n`&& cmdpreview_may_show(s)) { `\n\nwon't run if the buffer is not modifiable, this makes it that so by default I can't add incremental previews for quickfix in custom user commands\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nvim.opt.icm = \"split\"\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_user_command(\"PreviewTest\", function() end, {\n\tpreview = function()\n\t\tvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(0, 0, -1, false, { \"if you see this it works\" })\n\t\treturn 2\n\tend,\n})\n```\n\n`:set modifiable` works\n`:set nomodifiable` does not work\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nI would expect incremental preview to work with nomodifiable buffers.\n\nBut I understand that it kinda makes sense to skip nomodifiable, because incremental preview should in theory change the buffer. But the preview function would just fail at that point and the plugin author is responsible that it wouldn't do that\n\nAnyway, while I don't like it, this workaround works\n\n```lua\n\tvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"CmdlineEnter\", {\n\t\tcallback = function()\n\t\t\tvim.bo.modifiable = true \n\t\tend,\n\t})\n\tvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"CmdlineLeave\", {\n\t\tcallback = function()\n\t\t\tvim.bo.modifiable = false \n\t\tend,\n\t})\n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.10.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, does not have this functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ntmux\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nscreen256\n\n### Installation\n\npacman / tested with it built with source also\n\n### Extra notes\n\nI think that this should be in the help page (\"Please note that incremental preview is skipped on nomodifiable buffers\") ",
